Ah right I hadn&#x27;t seen this. From this line<p>&quot;A nanoscopic progress bar. Featuring realistic trickle animations to convince your users that something is happening!&quot;<p>You could do the same with progre(c)ss. And do it purely with CSS. Essentially that is what I am doing with the proge(c)ss bars on the page, I am using a keyframe animation and just setting different times on it.<p>Something like<p><pre><code>       @keyframes progress {
           0% {width: 0%;}
           100% {width: 100%;}
       }
</code></pre>
Then simply assign the animation to the :after element of a current progre(c)ss and there you have it without needing js.<p>Thanks for the heads up on nprogess, hadn&#x27;t seen it before.
